1. Hum sirf State badal rahe hain, Data Structure nahi
Backtracking mein pop_back() ki zaroorat tab padti hai jab aap koi global ya shared data structure (jaise vector<int>& current_combination) pass kar rahe ho aur aapko usme se elements ko dalkar ya nikal kar check karna ho (jaise Subset Sum ya Permutations problems mein).

Is code mein, aap koi array ya vector update nahi kar rahe hain. Aap sirf functional parameters (i aur amount) ko pass kar rahe hain.

Jab aap solve(i, coins, amount - coins[i]) call karte hain, toh computer ke memory stack (Call Stack) mein ek naya state banta hai jisme amount ki value temporary kam ho jaati hai.

Jab wo function call khatam (return) hoti hai, toh purana state khud-ba-khud active ho jaata hai jahan amount pehle jaisa hi rehta hai. Isko hum Implicit Backtracking via Call Stack kehte hain.
*/
